     ,"SAMPLE":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["A Li-7 implanted into Al target with (6.6+-0.4)E+17"
		,"Li-7/cm**2 was used for the measurement of angular"
		,"distributions for Li-7(p,a)."
		,"Excitation functions for both Li reactions were"
		,"measured with three targets- two LiF targets-"
		," (6.1+-0.2)*E+17 Li-7/cm**2 and (9.0+-0.4)*E+17 Li-7/"
		," cm**2- vacuum-evaporated on Ag and Cu backing( Li of"
		," natural isotopic composition-92.58% Li-7, 7.42% Li-6)"
		," and the Li-7 implanted into Al target, which were"
		," positioned inside the target chamber."]
	}
      ]
     ,"METHOD":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4codes":[{"code":"BCINT", "dict":"METHOD", "idict":21,"hlp":"Beam current integrated"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" The beam current on target was kept below"
		," 200 nA."]
	}
	,{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4codes":[{"code":"SITA", "dict":"METHOD", "idict":21,"hlp":"Single target irradiation"}]
	}
      ]
     ,"COMMENT":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["*By authors*.The effective energy E within the target"
		,"was derived from the incident energy of the ion beam"
		,"and the energy loss of the beam in the target."]
	}
      ]
     ,"ERR-ANALYS":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4code":{"header":"ERR-1"
	     ,"headerHelp":"1st partial uncertainty, defined under ERR-ANALYS"}
	,"x4freetext":[". The quoted uncertainties for S(E) arise from"
		,"uncertainty in the number of incident protons, measured"
		,"by a charge integrator and was obtained as 4%."
		,"The statistical uncertainty associated with N(E(o),ang-"
		,"lab)."]
	}
	,{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4code":{"header":"ERR-2"
	     ,"headerHelp":"2nd partial uncertainty, defined under ERR-ANALYS"}
	,"x4freetext":[".A 5% uncertainty in stopping cross sections"
		," affects not only S(E) but also the effective energy."
		," However, simulations show that the 5% uncertainty"
		," propagates into very small variations in energy-"
		," less 0.5% and in S(E) less 3.7%."]
	}
	,{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4code":{"header":"ERR-3"
	     ,"headerHelp":"3rd partial uncertainty, defined under ERR-ANALYS"}
	,"x4freetext":[".The uncertainty associated with the measurement"
		,"of the angular distributions is very small, less than"
		," 0.2%."
		,"These uncertainties were added quadratically."]
	}
